column5: LOL.  But right now, I'm working on finding a leak in the basement of the house...      I noticed there is no icon for how I feel right now...  Tomorrow is going to be such a loooong day cause of this...  :killme:
*bump* anyone else going?
see you all there
Have FUN guys and gal... catch a nice Rainbow trout for me!!!! That is what you're after correct.. they are much more fun than them wet bags!
I agree whole heartedly with that Wayne.  But I'm sure they'll have fun anyway.......
We'll be thinking about you Wayne.  Take care. Oh, and I would be happy with a rianbow trout...

We can catch spotted carp any old time of the year   ... but it's really only this time of year that you can set the hook on a big ole wet sock! Wayne, really sorry that you can't make it this year, completely understandable, I'm sure they need you more than we do! Take care and we'll connect when we get back. HH
Well.. Lloyd's up to 16 of them big socks as of 13:10 EST !
That's an aweful lot of spotted carp! HH
Lloyd got 19 today
This is almost as good as live stream.LOL
GET THE BUTTER!
Terry.. any takers on the spot yet??? I haven't got a text from Lloyd so I assume it's still open and will bump the thread.
still open
One day was way to short for me,  if this seat goes unattended,what a waste.
anyone sitting on the fence for this should jump on it!  it's going to be one hell of a weekend!
at least were being honest! lol
Okay, that's too bad, a bunch of us are going to be there if you change your mind.  Joey
True....True...
Hey joey it was J.J'S TEXAS GRILL
WE WERE THERE SAT NIGHT FOR DINNER IT WAS GOOD $22 BUT LEFT HUNGRY
Well if you'd rather go to another place Lloyd, let me know.  And thanks Memart!

No poker in your neighbor hood WalleyeJack...........but maybe poker in Picton. I guess we should pack the chips. We booked this weekend fishing long before the poker tourney. 36 hr's to go............can't wait!!!  Safe Fishing First, Jack
You could have ordered more food....
I've got to get a pic of me and Lloyd so I can tell everyone I met Ted's long lost brother...
I can't make it, my motor is still not repaired......

Joey knows Terry and mine's cell #'s.. she'll keep us up to date... well at least I think you will Hun.. no??  Just not toooo late for supper reservations... that Damn Lloydo'clock just comes way toooo early!  YES.. I'll be there... as much as I shouldn't, considering lost work days for nothing this week, I need to blow off some steam!

So glad you can make it Wayne.  I think we should meet for dinner there around 5 or 6 then. Should be good and hungry by then after a day on the water.  So lets go with that plan and we'll firm up on Saturday by phone  Joey

Lloyd.. what time say you for supper??? 5:30.. 6:00 ??  So come on guys/gals.... lets get a serious count so Joey can make Reservations for us all.  Lloyd, Terry, Jose, Paul and myself for the first 5.
Joey, Paul and Roy makes 8.
we like leftovers on your way back
LOL Geoff.. you guys are in the middle of nowhere over there at Perfect Vue !
but we should be well into the "I have the munchies" attitude by then, or even before dinner... duno...  lol
lets say 6 pm sat night
Okay Lloyd ! Joey.. maybe start at thread.. BOQ.. Saturday night dinner @ 6pm @ ______  and get a head count?!?
Yes Boss
Sorry.. just use to a good women taking care of my meals !!
and a morning workout?
Hey Geoff: while they are all over at JJ's why dont we get everyone who has eatin my wife's chili to go over to there motel and we can baby sit there rooms for them?

Sorry folks we are just too far away to meet for supper.. Not to mention the ferry.. (whom we have already determined)  LOL  but 3+ hours is far too much for just supper.   You guys have a great time though! and hopefully we have a chance to say hello!  G
SO who is going who is going with you  where are you staying  do you want to get together at a fire Saturday night  or a restaurant one night  do you have a fire pit where you are staying

UMMMM.  Hopefully Terry is going with me.  Probably in the same room with Terry.. maybe that Jose guy..  Picton Harbour Inn  If I'm there... who's the DD to get to the fire?  Be a much longer drive to Perfect View from Picton.. than it was from Deseronto..  You know the situation Terry.. you plan it.. I'll try to attend it!
I'm in with Headhunter and crew at Perfect Vue.  We still need a spot in a boat for Skeeter...

yeah  I didn't say I was going to go to the fire , I just figured many would and we needed someone to start a thread  cause I think it was last year or the year before that we got asked out to diner with the gang in the evening after we had already ate ..  so I thought people could get some things going here....  and if you want, I would be the DD but someone has to yeah when I need to turn the wheel or hit the brake...LOL.......I will drink coke that night the rum can stay in the bottle
good luck with everthing...lol  Hope ya catch a ton.
I'AM IN  Picton Inn friday@saturday night  friend from quebec is meeting up with us  fire or bar no matter.
Paul, Roy and I will be at Merlands.  I think going out for dinner would be nice, then fire later - wherever!!  So who wants to go for dinner?  Joey

OrangePeel will be there Thurs thru Sunday. Pete, Rick and I will be staying at the Picton Harbour Inn. None of us drink so you might talk us in to driving. Drop by an say hello, we are on the main floor.  Safe Fishing First, Jack
You guys leave the town in one piece and leave some fish for me. I'm in the Picton Harbor Inn suit upstairs, 15,16,17,18 Good luck guys.
we are there the weekend after you...make sure you leave some fish for us
Have a look for us FishFarmer..........we could use any help we can get. We will be on the water with the sunrise on Thurs. Channel 68 on the vhf.  Safe Fishing First, Jack
see you all there  tic tic tic  just counting down the days

You can be sure of that Terry, the way my luck has been down there, I don't need the camera. I'll be posting when I get back. You guys may be gone by then.  OrangePeal, look for the blue and white Princecraft with 4 guys in it and the Perch Festival black Lund. I'll try and remember to put the VHF radio on. Just give us a call. most of the time we have the FRS radio's on. First day I think were putting in at Bath.
We have the name on the side of the cruiser. 27ft. with 3 guys onboard. We will likely put in Picton and head out right away.  The clock is ticking.......but it seems slow.  Safe Fishing First, Jack
~~~If the weather holds I'll be down for the Sat, launching at the ferry Ramp, Green Tracker
hope it changes   Nov. 17 ThursdayW 45 km/h    Nov. 18 FridayNW 25 km/h   Nov. 19 SaturdaySW 30 km/h
Showin snow for Sunday! But don't worry.. a few more US planes laying down chemtrails this week and that will all change!
counting down the days
P-Vue crew: Cabin 5: Headhunter, Fishnsled, Gerritt, Bitsmith, Skeeter and me. Cabin 3: LincolnG (+ two buddies) and young_one.  Can't wait!
cant wait ...me too
See you guys out there! White Tracker with kicker and 150 Merc. Finger crossed for calmer weather.
Jack, no poker tourney Friday night for you and Pete ?
Look for the beige PolarCraft flying the OFC Flag!

So I guess Saturday night will be the Trophy handoff to the 2010 winner  Is everyone going to meet at a restaurant Sat. night?  The one we went to last year was great and could accomodate.  Can't remember the name tho.  Lex, you remember?  Joey
From the 60+ emails our crew has be blasting back and forth today...  I have a funny feeling none of us can drive by that time...
